<HEAD>Barry Filed Federal Tax Returns Late</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 District of <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION> Mayor <PERSON> Marion </PERSON> <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> filed his federal income tax returns late in the early 1980s even though he had a refund coming each year, according to <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>. The newspaper quoted an unnamed source as saying that <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> waited until 1986 to file his 1982, 1983 and 1984 federal returns. Other sources told the <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> that <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> filed several returns in 1986 but could not confirm the years. <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> declined a request by the newspaper to be interviewed about his tax returns. His press secretary, <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON>, released a statement that <PERSON> Barry </PERSON>'s returns are filed every year. `` First, my taxes are a personal matter between myself and the federal and district governments. Second, my taxes are filed every year by my accountant in the year in which they are due. Third, it is a violation of law for someone to give out my tax returns other than myself,'' <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> said in a statement. The mayor, who has refused to publicly release copies of his tax returns since he was elected in 1978, filed late `` largely because of procrastination,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION>, in its Tuesday editions, quoted one of <PERSON> Barry </PERSON>'s associates as saying. Failure to file a federal income tax return is a misdemeanor and each count carries a possible one-year prison sentence. Although <PERSON> Barry </PERSON>'s federal returns for 1982, 1983 and 1984 were late, he apparently filed his <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> returns on time for those years, the <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> said. <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> records show that <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> filed his 1982, 1983 and 1984 returns in the year in which each return was due, according a source familier with District tax records. <PERSON> Barry </PERSON> received <LOCATION> D.C. </LOCATION> refunds for each of the years except 1982.
