needed to stop cross-border drug trafficking. Among the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION> sample, the figure was 73 percent. The poll showed that 71 percent of <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> voters approved a proposal to charge a $ 1 or $ 2 border crossing fee to finance more <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> inspectors at the border.
