<HEAD>House Passes DeControl Bill</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> approved on Monday a bill to remove remaining federal price controls on natural gas. The measure, passed and sent to the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> by voice vote, removes all price controls at the wellhead. However, the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Regulatory </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> would retain the power to regulate rates charged by interstate natural gas pipelines and states would retain their regulatory powers over consumer prices. Most gas from wells drilled after the enactment of the 1978 Natural Gas Policy Act has been decontrolled for several years. The new legislation would gradually remove controls from `` old gas,'' that from wells predating the 1978 act.
