<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The $ 1 billion sale of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION> movie studio to <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> has been approved by the Quintex board of directors, the company announced today. The deal, in essence, will split the present <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and leave majority shareholder <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> in control of the MGM portion of the business. The renamed <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> would be the first big American motion picture studio to pass into foreign hands. Australian-turned-U.S. citizen <PERSON> Rupert </PERSON> <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON> owns 20th <ORGANIZATION> Century </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Film </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> through his <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Entertainment </ORGANIZATION> is a TV company that financed part of the <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> miniseries `` Lonesome Dove'' and bills itself as <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s largest independent TV production and distribution <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION>, one of the five dominant <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> movie studios, holds the rights to 4,000 movies, including the `` The Pink Panther'' and <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Bond </PERSON> series and Rocky films. The sale agreement calls for <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> to pay $ 20 a share, or about $ 1 billion, for <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>. Financier <PERSON> Kirkorian </PERSON>, who holds 82 percent of <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> stock, then will buy back <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> assets for $ 250 million. Included in the `` new'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> will be movie and TV production assets and a library of 34 recent films, including `` Moonstruck'' and `` A Fish Called <PERSON> Wanda </PERSON>.'' The deal is expected to close in late summer. <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> lost $ 39.5 million in the first quarter of its 1989 fiscal year. The loss was attributed to increased interest expense and high write-offs on movies in production and already released.
