<HEAD>Judge Refuses To Dismiss Lawsuit By Ethanol Producers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DANVILLE, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal judge has refused to dismiss a $ 2.1 billion antitrust lawsuit filed by fuel alcohol producers against four major oil companies. <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> on Friday rejected the oil companies' argument that the ethanol producers were not in competition with them and therefore had no financial interest that would lead them to sue. Seven ethanol producers allege that the oil companies _ <ORGANIZATION> Marathon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Shell </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> AMOCO </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and <ORGANIZATION> Chevron </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> U.S.A. </ORGANIZATION> _ conspired to ruin the market for gasohol, a blend of 90 percent gasoline and 10 percent ethanol. Attorney <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Wright </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Lafayette </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> La. </LOCATION>, representing the plaintiffs, has argued that the oil companies tried to `` retard'' the growth of the ethanol industry. The judge ruled the oil companies and the ethanol producers were in competition for the non-diesel automobile fuel market. The ethanol makers contend the oil companies used signs on their gasoline pumps saying such things as `` our gasoline contains no alcohol or ethanol'' to discourage motorists from using gasohol. Ethanol, which can be made from corn, increases the octane of gasoline and reduces pollution in automobile emissions, according to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Growers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>. The plaintiffs are <ORGANIZATION> Greater </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rockford </ORGAN