<HEAD>With LaserPhoto NXJ1</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DEAN GOLEMBESKI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 It's a long way from Wall Street to the 6th floor of <ORGANIZATION> Bridgeport </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Superior </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, but a lawsuit being heard here is being closely watched by stockbrokers. Closing arguments are to begin Tuesday in a legal dispute that pits <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> against one of the so-called `` superbrokers'' it hired away from competitors in the early 1980s, most from <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kuhn </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Loeb </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. Five of the brokers were fired in 1984 They filed suit against <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> and its parent, <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, claiming the investment firm lured them away just to capture their multimillion dollar client base. Four of the brokers agreed to arbitration before the case could go to trial in federal court in <LOCATION> Manhattan </LOCATION>, but <PERSON> Geoffrey </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Winters </PERSON> pursued the case and is asking for at least $ 16 million in damages. He claims he was fired unjustly. The case ended up in the <LOCATION> Connecticut </LOCATION> courts after <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> obtained a lien against <ORGANIZATION> Winters </ORGANIZATION>' <LOCATION> Greenwich </LOCATION> home to recover a $ 300,000 signing bonus he was to repay if he was fired within four years because of poor performance. <PERSON> Perrin </PERSON> <PERSON> Long </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Lipper </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Analytical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said <LOCATION> Wall </LOCATION> <LOCATI