<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Rising sales in <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s automotive and information systems segments helped lead to a first-quarter earnings increase of 4 percent, the company said Monday. <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said earnings during the period that ended March 31 totaled $ 69 million or $ 1.12 a share, up from $ 66 million or $ 1.07 during the same quarter a year ago. `` Each of our major segments reported operating profits equal to or better than the year-earlier period when we experienced particularly strong results,'' said <PERSON> Joseph </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Gorman </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive officer. `` This quarter's earnings improvement was attained in what we believe was a much tougher competitive environment.'' <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said sales in its space and defense segment dropped 5 percent from $ 815 to $ 775 million because of previously announced program changes and reductions. However, operating profit in that segment rose nearly 2 percent from $ 58 million to $ 59 million, the company said. Sales in the automotive segment rose 10 percent from $ 787 million to $ 868 million, <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said, attributing the increase to improved business in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. Operating profit in the segment remained at $ 745 million, <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said. In the information systems segment, sales rose 12 percent from $ 126 million to $ 141 million, <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said. It noted particularly strong performances in the consumer credit reporting and image-based data processing businesses. Operating profit rose 51 percent from $ 9 million to $ 13 million in information systems, the company said. <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION>, which provides high technology produces and services, said sales overall for the quarter dropped 1 percent from $ 1.8 billion to $ 1.79 billion. Excluding sales for businesses divested last year, sales rose 4 percent, <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> said.
