gest food companies in the country with revenues of $ 9.4 billion last year. The asset-option agreement between <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> allows <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION> to purchase about one-third of <PERSON> Holly </PERSON>'s assets at prices already negotiated if the <LOCATION> Memphis </LOCATION> company is bought by anyone else within the next nine months. <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON> contends the asset agreement was an illegal attempt to make <ORGANIZATION> Holly </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Farms </ORGANIZATION> unattractive to any buyer other than <ORGANIZATION> ConAgra </ORGANIZATION>. The <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> judge hearing <PERSON> Tyson </PERSON>'s suit has blocked any execution of the asset agreement until the legal disputes surrounding it are settled.
